3M, Cisco share losses lead Dow's 75-point fall

Shares of 3M and Cisco are retreating Thursday morning, sending the Dow Jones Industrial Average into negative territory. Shares of 3M MMM, -2.14% and Cisco CSCO, -2.96% are contributing to the blue-chip gauge's intraday decline, as the Dow DJIA, -2.29% was most recently trading 79 points, or 0.3%, lower. 3M's shares are off $3.70, or 2.2%, while those of Cisco are off $0.42 (1.0%), combining for a roughly 28-point drag on the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the decline are Johnson & Johnson JNJ, -0.87%, Dow Inc. DOW, -2.84%, and Pfizer PFE, -0.68%. A $1 move in any of the index's 30 components equates to a 6.78-point swing.